post_text:
A reminder to all our families that schools start this Monday, August 17th for ALL students!

Students with the last names A through K will be attending in-person, while all other students will be e-learning. Those students attending physically starting Monday should have an email with bus stop location, times, and other transportation information. Please email our transportation director at amyers@rbbschools.net to correct any information.

Students attending in-person beginning Thursday, August 20, will receive emails with transportation information at the beginning of the week.

Students attending the virtual academies begin on Monday as well!

Looking forward to a certainly unique but super successful school year for all Edgewood schools!!!

post_text: At R-BB we value strong community and industry partnerships that will prepare our students to contribute to their community in meaningful ways. Thanks to the hard work of many and the support of Regional Opportunity Initiatives, Inc. we have designed a plan to develop the experiences students need for workforce readiness, and we are thrilled to begin implementing the plans at every level!

post_text:
Please pass the word that KG Registration is different this year and that we have started the process TODAY for current families in the RBB district! Families new to RBB are invited to start coming in on Monday, Feb. 3.

The office is open DAILY 9:30 - 1 for parents to drop in for about 15 minutes to fill out paperwork. Once the paperwork is completed, a day will be scheduled for parents and their child to come back for a low-stress & fun assessment and tour. This will take about 45 minutes.

If you have questions, you can call EPS at 812-876-9600 between the hours of 9:30 - 2, when the office staff is less busy with arrival/dismissal procedures.

More information is on the flyer below. We can't wait to see you!

shared_text:
Edgewood FFA and Agriculture Program
June 19, 2019 at 10:17 AM Â·

In case you missed our story yesterday...we had an awesome time at the 90th Indiana FFA State Convention at Purdue University!

We started our day with a leadership workshop geared towards building a strong team! From there we headed to a private tour of the Purdue Butcher Block in the new Land Oâ€™Lakes Building! Thank you H.D. Smith for the hookup!! While we were there two members, our designated Chapter Delegates Landen and Wesley, headed to complete some CANstruction community service with the Food Finders!

We then headed over to the Columbia Park Zoo to mingle with all sorts of animals including the tiniest baby goat!

A nice(aka messy) dinner at Texas Roadhouse and then we finished the night at the Opening Session listening to the hilarious and inspirational keynote speaker - Wiley Bailey!

Big thanks to everyone that made this possible! We enjoyed our sweet ride, big thanks to Vickie Coffey!

Join us for our Free Summer Feeding at RBB!!!

Free healthy breakfast and lunch meals this summer to all children up to the age of 18. Our meals will be provided Monday through Friday at Edgewood Primary School through June 28th and again, July 8th through July 26th. Breakfast hours are 9:30 a.m. until 10:00 a.m. and lunch will be served from 12:00 p.m. until 1:30 p.m. Meals are FREE for all children. For the past two-and-a-half years, EPS and EIS have been working towards STEM certification. Last fall we submitted a lengthy application and a STEM certification team from the state visited our schools. I am pleased to share that EPS and EIS have both been awarded full STEM Certification from the state of Indiana.

While we are thrilled to have reached this milestone, our teachers continue to be involved in professional development throughout the school year and into the summer.

Please consider joining us on Thursday, May 9th, from 6:00-7:30 at EPS and EIS for our STEAM Fest to see the many projects our students have completed this year. Food trucks will be here at 5:30.

Thank you for your faithful support of our students!

Check out Indiana's nine "CCR&Rs" -- they are here to make sure children throughout the state get a great start!

post_text: All RBBCSC schools are closed today Friday, January 12 due to weather. Reminder that school is also closed on Monday, January 15 due to Martin Luther King Jr. Day. Please be safe this weekend. Students will report back on Tuesday, January 16.

post_text:
School is on a 2 hour delay tomorrow, Friday, January 5th due to the forecast of negative temperatures, and double-digit wind chill temperatures. Students should arrive 2 hours after their scheduled start time.
A call from Dr. Wilcox will go out at 5 p.m. today. If you do not get this call by later this evening (as it takes a few minutes for all calls to go out), please check Harmony and update all numbers and email addresses that may have changed.
